<subSubSection id="FC8E653B875AB100137C55ADF624FA9C" pageId="21" pageNumber="214" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875AB100137C55ADF6BBFBDB" blockId="21.[2085,2678,959,1377]" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875AB100137C55ADF755FC25" bold="true" box="[2085,2241,959,984]" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB100139555ADF7FEFC02" authority="Merriam, 1894" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1894" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="214" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenarius">Perognathus arenarius Merriam, 1894</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED875AB100132055CCF6BBFBDB" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894301" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">near Comondu, San Jorge, Baja California Sur, Mexico.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875AB100137F523FF624FA9C" blockId="21.[2085,2678,959,1377]" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">
Based on detailed sequencing of nDNA and mtDNA genes, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB10012115246F67CFB88" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" box="[2376,2536,1108,1141]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenarius">C. arenarius</taxonomicName>
is a close relative of C. ammophilus and 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB100129D526EF5A5FB60" baseAuthorityName="Osgood" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[2500,2609,1148,1181]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="siccus">C. siccus</taxonomicName>
, and all three are part of the Baja California Peninsula lineage of the “modern” clade of coarse-haired pocket mice, along with 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB10013715330F708FAC6" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[2088,2204,1314,1339]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="214" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fallax">C. fallax</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB10013EE5330F6E1FAC6" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[2231,2421,1314,1339]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="215" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="californicus">C. californicus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB100128F5330F5FBFAC6" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[2518,2671,1314,1339]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spinatus">C. spinatus</taxonomicName>
. Nine subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
